Buenos dias. Estoy con algunas pruebas para soporte CURL #include "<http://hbcurl.ch|hbcurl.ch>"

function main()
	
	local hCurl, cBuffer := ""
	local aData := {}
	local cUrl 	:= "<https://picsum.photos/v2/list?page=2&limit=10>"
	local cHtml := ""
	local n, aHeaders

	curl_global_init()	

	if ! empty( hCurl := curl_easy_init() )

		curl_easy_setopt( hCurl, HB_CURLOPT_URL, cUrl )
      curl_easy_setopt( hCurl, HB_CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER, .f. )
      curl_easy_setopt( hCurl, HB_CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST, .f. )
      curl_easy_setopt( hCurl, HB_CURLOPT_NOPROGRESS, .f. )
      //curl_easy_setopt( hCurl, HB_CURLOPT_VERBOSE, .T. )
      curl_easy_setopt( hCurl, HB_CURLOPT_DL_BUFF_SETUP )

		if curl_easy_perform(hCurl) == 0
			cBuffer := curl_easy_dl_buff_get( hCurl )
			? cBuffer
			if !empty(cBuffer)
				hb_jsonDecode( cBuffer, @aData )
			endif
		endif
	endif

	curl_global_cleanup()

	? hb_jsonEncode( aData, .T. )	// T=pretty

return NIL

//----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------//

text: Checks whether the client will send data and invites it to continue, if necessary (by sending a 100 Continue response if the client is HTTP 1.1 or higher). Returns 1 if the client should send data; 0 if not. ap_setup_client_block( ) should be called before this function, and this function should be called before ap_ get_client_block(). This function should only be called once. It should also not be called until we are ready to receive data from the client.
